- Scope: `ai-service`
- Short Description:
  - Support multi-vehicle detection and improve OCR accuracy by relaxing regex bounds.

## Problem Context / Root Cause
- Current behavior:
  - The pipeline only detects one vehicle per image and OCR misses some plates due to strict word boundaries (\b).
- Expected behavior:
  - System extracts all vehicles in an image, crops each, and accurately performs OCR. OCR should handle slight noise.
- Root cause:
  - detect_vehicle returned only the top confidence result. _ID_PLATE_PATTERN used \b which failed when OCR detected noise alongside the plate text.

### Changed Areas
- ai-service/app/models/schemas.py
- ai-service/app/services/analyzer.py
- ai-service/app/services/plate_reader.py
- ai-service/app/services/vehicle_detector.py
- ai-service/app/scripts/build_index.py

