## Detailed Changes
### 1) What Changed
- File-level summary:
  - schemas.py: Replaced single vehicle properties with a list of VehicleDetection objects in AnalyzeResponse.
  - vehicle_detector.py: Changed detect_vehicle to return a list of all vehicles exceeding the confidence threshold.
  - plate_reader.py: Relaxed the regex pattern _ID_PLATE_PATTERN by removing \b.
  - analyzer.py: Refactored to iterate over the detected_vehicles array, running OCR on cropped vehicle images independently.
  - build_index.py: Adapted to consume the new detect_vehicle list output.
- Behavior-level summary:
  - The API now returns a vehicles array, allowing multiple license plates to be extracted from a single image. OCR is more robust to noise.

### 2) Why This Approach
- Best practice dictates encapsulating vehicle properties into distinct objects. Expanding to multi-vehicle detection maximizes value extraction per image. Removing \b easily prevents OCR false-negatives due to random spacing/noise without complex post-processing.

